FBIS4-18683 "drweu068_j_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-068 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Observers in Hebron To Have `Political Function' Observers in Hebron To Have `Political Function' LD0604123994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1100 GMT 6 Apr 94 LD0604123994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri stressed that "the functions of the Italian observers in Hebron will essentially be political, and to provide security for the local population." "The fact that all the sides asked for our soldiers to take part in the operation along side troops from Denmark and Norway," Fabbri added, "shows how much prestige Italy has acquired during these peacekeeping operations." Referring to Somalia, the minister said, "It was the most demanding operation that our troops have taken part in since the Second World War, because of the loss of life that we endured."
